      },
      "date": "2022-06-13 20:57:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nChris, there wasn't a Fixes: label on the original version of this patch, but it is useful to include the Fixes label on all patches when possible so it is more clear to understand when this bug was introduced (e.g. is this a regression in 2.15 or a pre-existing issue), and if it needs to be backported to e.g. b2_12 or similar.\n\nLooking at \"git blame\" for this function, it appears that this has existed since the original commit v2_10_52_0-19-g0f1aaad4c1, so should get:\n\n Fixes: 0f1aaad4c1b (\"LU-9480 lnet: implement Peer Discovery\")\n\nunless there is some more recent patch that changed the calling convention and triggered this problem more frequently?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
