      },
      "date": "2022-06-15 22:18:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Chris, there wasn't a Fixes: label on the original version of this\n > patch, but it is useful to include the Fixes label on all patches\n > when possible so it is more clear to understand when this bug was\n > introduced (e.g. is this a regression in 2.15 or a pre-existing\n > issue), and if it needs to be backported to e.g. b2_12 or similar.\n > \n > Looking at \"git blame\" for this function, it appears that this has\n > existed since the original commit v2_10_52_0-19-g0f1aaad4c1, so\n > should get:\n > \n > Fixes: 0f1aaad4c1b (\"LU-9480 lnet: implement Peer Discovery\")\n > \n > unless there is some more recent patch that changed the calling\n > convention and triggered this problem more frequently?\n\nYeah, sorry I omitted the Fixes label on this one. I don't think there are any recent patches that would make it more likely to be hit. I only found the issue through code review. I've added your suggested Fixes label.",
